name: Theory of Everything prints: 01
description:
Theory of Everything  |  Beautiful Geometry

Circular interpretations of smoothly varying families of symmetry. A visual representation of the hypothetical theory of theoretical physics that explains and links together all known physical phenomena. Based on the Lie Groups, E7 and E8. Lie Groups play a huge role in modern geometry and represent the best developed theory of continuous symmetry of mathematical objects and structure.

Custom sizes and framed prints available, please contact for quotes.
Digital prints are printed on 300gsm matte paper.
Giclee fine art prints are printed on Entrada Cotton rag paper natural 300gsm. 
Photographic prints are printed on Lustre Kodak Supra Endura digital paper.

Please allow 1-3 weeks for print orders to arrive from date of payment.
